Lecture given on birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, April 12 (KNS-KCNA) -- The central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) sponsored a lecture meeting in Tokyo on Wednesday to commemorate the 88th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the meeting were first vice-chairman So Man Sul and chief vice-chairman Ho Jong Man of the Chongryon central standing committee and other officials of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants appreciated a video lecture "our leader had won victory after victory with songs."

Kim Il Sung's feats praised in Guinea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Boubacar Biro Diallo, president of the National Assembly of Guinea, highly praised the immortal exploits of the President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said President Kim Il Sung was the greatest leader of the 20th century and the feats performed by him will remain forever in history of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Il Sung founded the Juche idea with his outstanding ideological and theoretical wisdom and indicated the correctest way of shaping the destiny of the nation and humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The great Juche idea has proven its truth and validity as the guiding idea of the times in practice of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His Juche idea and feats are being brilliantly carried forward by General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Foreign embassy officials pay homage to Kim Il Sung
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of foreign embassies here visited the statue of the President Kim Il Sung on Mansu Hill in Pyongyang on Thursday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The visitors laid a basket of flowers before the statue and paid their respects to the President.

Festival participants pay respects to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Foreign and overseas Korean artistes, who are participating in the 18th April Spring Friendship Art Festival, on Thursday visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace at which the President Kim Il Sung lies in state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The visitors paid homage to his statue and went upstairs to make deep bow to him in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They looked round the wailers hall, a train and a car the President used for on-site guidance and foreign tour and in the last period of his life.

National seminar on Juche idea held in Nepal
   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A Nepalese national Juche idea seminar on the President Kim Il Sung's immortal exploits for the development of human ideology and the cause of independence was held in Kathmandu on April 2 on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his report at the seminar Manik Lal Shrestha, director of the Nepal Institute for Juche studies, said the Juche idea has become the beacon showing the road ahead of the popular masses, the guiding idea of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   President Kim Il Sung founded this idea, reflecting the requirement of the times and aspiration of the masses, the reporter said, adding his undying feats for the development of human ideology and the cause of independence will remain forever in the hearts of the world's progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Minister of State for Public Health Tir Tha Ram Dangol, who is a representative of the Nepalese government, said in his speech that the august name of the President shines all over the world as he gave the progressive humankind of the world the Juche idea indicating the correctest way of national liberation, independence, progress and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to General Secretary Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

Film show arranged for foreign embassy officials
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A film show for officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of foreign embassies in the DPRK was held here on Thursday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the show were acting chairman of the committee for cultural relations with foreign countries Mun Jae Chol and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants saw "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Meets With Heads of State and Prominent Personages of Different Countries" part 7 (January 1990-June 1994), a Korean documentary film recording his immortal exploits.

Commemorations of Sun's Day held abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Dhaka, Lima, Antananarivo and Rome from April 5 to 8 to commemorate Sun's Day, the birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speeches were made at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The chairman of the Peru-Korea Institute of Culture and Friendship said Kim Il Sung is a great man of the century and an eternal leader of humanity who devoted his whole life only to national prosperity and reunification and to the liberation of the world's oppressed people. He will always remain alive in the heart of humankind along with history of socialist Korea and of the world socialism, the speaker added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The vice-chairman of the Madagascar-Korea friendship and solidarity committee said that the world's progressives have highly praised, revered and followed Kim Il Sung as the great sun of the 20th century. Sun's Day, his birthday, is a holiday common to humankind, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The general secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist) said that the cause of Juche, the cause of socialism started by Kim Il Sung is now being carried forward and developed successfully under the wise guidance of the great Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meetings held in Bangladesh and Madagascar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, film shows were held in Nepal and Egypt, a film show and photo exhibition in Indonesia and Tanzania and a ceremony of starting a week of photo show took place in Guinea.

Sun's Day commemorated by international organization
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of laying a floral basket before the Portrait of the President Kim Il Sung took place at the building of the organization of solidarity of the peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America on April 7 on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the ceremony were the secretary-general of the executive secretariat and officials of the organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants laid a basket of flowers before the portrait of President Kim Il Sung and paid respects to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretary-general praised Kim Il Sung as a great leader who founded the great Juche idea and brightened, like beacon, the road ahead of peoples of Asia, Africa and Latin America. His idea and feats will shine forever, he stressed.

Syrian charge d'affaires ad interim hosts reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Syrian charge d'affaires ad interim here Haissam Saad hosted a reception at the embassy yesterday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said in his speech that the President Kim Il Sung founded the Juche idea, led the struggle against the most vicious imperialism to victory and devoted his whole life to the cause of building  the people-centred socialism of Korean style. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
   Kim Il Sung always supported the just struggle of the Syrian people, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The friendly relations between Syria and the DPRK are steadily developing amidst the deep concern of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and President Hafez al Assad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Juche idea will shine forever as the revolutionary idea of Kim Il Sung, a great revolutionary and great thinker. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Choe Thae Bok, alternate member of the political bureau and secretary of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea, said in his speech that Kim Il Sung always paid a deep attention to the struggle of the government and people of the Syrian Arab republic to defend the independence and sovereignty of the country against imperialism and Zionism, and build a new prosperous society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people will positively strive to further develop the friendly and cooperative relations with Syria established by Kim Il Sung in his lifetime and President Hafez al Assad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people sincerely wish the government and people of Syria greater success in their efforts to build an independent and modern Syria and solve the mid-east issue fairly and comprehensively under the correct leadership of Hafez al Assad.

Anniversary of Finland-Korea society marked
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A rally and photo exhibition were held here yesterday to mark the 30th anniversary of the foundation of the Finland-Korea Society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Jong Suk, editor-in-chief of Minju Joson and chairperson of the Korea-Finland Friendship Association, in her speech said that the inland-Korea society has made energetic efforts in the past 30 years to develop friendly relations between the two peoples and support the Korean people in their struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The society made a great contribution to donating a lot of humanitarian aid materials and valuable scientific and technical materials to the DPRK in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Anna Liisa Jokinen, former member of the parliament and head of a Finnish friendship delegation, in her speech said that the President Kim Il Sung was, is and will always be with us and will lead the Korean revolution and the world revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The great revolutionary exploits of the President are being successfully carried forward and accomplished by leader Kim Jong Il who is identical with the President in ideology, leadership and personality, she said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The exploits of Kim Jong Il, who set forth the unique mode of the army-first politics and leads socialism of Korea to victory, will shine long down through generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The society will continue to invariably support and encourage the Korean people in their just cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She expressed the belief that the Korean people would achieve great success in building a powerful socialist country and in their just struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country under the outstanding and seasoned leadership of the great Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Before the rally the participants looked round photos introducing Finland.

Foreign embassy officials visit Mangyongdae and Kimilsungia Show 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- The foreign military attaches' corps in the DPRK visited Mangyongdae, the birth place of the President Kim Il Sung, on Thursday with the approach of Sun's Day, his birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The guests called at the President's native home in Mangyongdae and looked round relics there with keen interest, being briefed on the fact that he was born and cultivated the great ambition of the revolution, spending his childhood there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They climbed Mangyong hill to go round the revolutionary sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Then they went to the second Kimilsungia show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, the foreign economic and commercial councilors' corps here visited the show on the same day.

Kim Il Sung's revolutionary exploits off press
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Vol. 20 "Successful Solution of Issue of Succession to the Revolutionary Cause" of the library "the Immortal Revolutionary Exploits of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" came off the press at the Worker's Party of Korea Publishing House on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The book has three chapters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chapter one deals with the ideological and theoretical exploits President Kim Il Sung performed by setting forth the original idea and theory on the issue of succession to the revolutionary cause for the first time in the history of human thought and steadily developing them in depth to systematize them in an integral way, and proves its greatness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chapter two profoundly explains the wise and great leadership of the President who, regarding the issue of succession to the revolutionary cause of Juche as a question of principle related to the destiny of the worker's party and revolution of Korea, admirably solved the issue in a unique manner in conformity with the fundamental principle of carrying out the cause of independence of the popular masses and the lawful requirements of the developing Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chapter three clearly explains the enduring  historical significance of Kim Il Sung's successful solution of the issue of succession to the revolutionary cause in carrying out the cause of socialism and communism and in carving out the destiny of the world's revolutionary people.

Separate and group performances of Pyongyang festival close
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- separate and group  performances of the 18th April spring friendship art festival, which raised the curtain on April 11 on the occasion of Sun's Day, closed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Foreign artistes and overseas. Korean artistes created and put on the stage many art works including "Song of Sun's Day", "Spring In Alien Land" and "When Thinking of the Leader," eulogizing the glorious life of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The festival stage was colorfully decorated by many art works highly praising General Secretary Kim Jong Il as the hope of humankind and the sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Also put on the stage were art works singing of the revolutionary achievements of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese heroine and indomitable communist revolutionary fighter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Performers sang songs "Green Pine Standing On Nam Hill," "Song of Comradeship," "Rainbow of Reunification" and so on which are favorite among the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Foreigners' dances, songs, instrumental music and other art works represent the traditional and national customs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
"Song of Revolution," "Friendship," "Yearning For Girl," "Echo of Love," "KalGnka" and other dances and songs were acclaimed by the audiences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Acrobats adorned the festival stage with colorful numbers full of inexhaustible human creative power, wisdom, bravery and boldness, optimism and stamina of youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The festival goes on with joint performances.

Joint national meeting of Korean children's union organizations
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A joint national meeting of the Korean Children's Union organizations was held in the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace today to commemorate the 88th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Attending the meeting were representatives of provincial KCU organizations and schoolchildren in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Paek Hak Rim, Kim Jung Rin, officials concerned, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, veterans of the Fatherland Liberation War, men of merit, parents of schoolchildren and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants made a deep bow to the President with unbounded reverence for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ri Il Hwan, first secretary of the central committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The reporter referred to the warm love of the President who preferentially gave the best things to children, calling them "king" of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He stressed that all the KCU members should study harder and harder under the slogan "let us learn for Korea " and prepare themselves to be reserves for building a powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
An accession ceremony to the KCU took place at the meeting.

Foreign trade unions hail three-point charter of Korea's reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Representatives of 30 trade unions of 25 countries to the 14th WFTU congress held in New Delhi from March 25 to 28 participated in the signature campaign for support to the three-point charter of Korea's reunification in accordance with the resolution of the congress on solidarity with the workers and other people of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The signature paper was signed by secretary general of the Center of Indian Trade Unions M. Kpandey on behalf of three million members, vice-chairman of the Yugoslav Federation of Autonomous Trade Unions Dobrika Savis on behalf of two million members and chairman of the general center of the Brazilian workers Antonio Neto on behalf of 1,200,000 members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was also signed by representatives of trade unions of Sri Lanka, Lebanon, Libya, Angola, Peru, Venezuela, Greece, Spain, Australia and other countries in the name of their organizations.

National meeting held 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the 6,000-seat theatre of the April 25 House of Culture today to commemorate the 88th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present there were Jo Myong Rok, Hong Song Nam and other senior officials of the party and the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among those present were diplomatic envoys here, foreign guests and overseas compatriots staying in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Yang Hyong Sop, alternate politburo member of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and vice-president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that April 15, the birthday of President Kim Il Sung, is the most auspicious holiday that brought the greatest fortune to the Korean nation and the world's revolutionary people, who yearned for human dignity and a true life, groaning under domination, subjugation and oppression for ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   President Kim Il Sung was a prominent leader in the era of independence and remains the sun of revolution for he glorified the 20th century as a new one by bringing about a radical turn in hewing out the destiny of the Korean nation and humankind, he noted, adding: Kim Il Sung led the anti-imperialist national liberation struggle, anti-imperialist, anti-feudal democratic revolution, the socialist revolution and socialist construction to victory in the van of the revolutionary struggle of the working class for a long period from the 1920s to the mid-1990s recorded with breath-taking events, thus performing outstanding exploits in the history of the struggle for human emancipation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pointing out that he fathered the immortal Juche idea for the first time in the history reflecting the demand of the times and the desire of humankind, thereby ushering in a new era of independence in which the popular masses independently shape their own destiny, the reporter said that the President founded the Worker's Party of Korea and strengthened and developed it as a powerful leading political organization, and his feats and experience gained in party construction clearly proved the universal truth of the revolution that people's struggle is sure to win despite any ups and downs, only when there is a powerful, veteran revolutionary party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that the President founded true revolutionary armed forces capable of defending freedom and happiness of the people  and this is a distinguished exploit he made by building up a reliable driving force for the accomplishment of the cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is thanks to the powerful revolutionary armed forces built by the President that the WPK and the Korean people are successfully carrying out the socialist cause despite the desperate moves of the imperialist allied forces and reactionaries to isolate and stifle the DPRK, he stressed, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President pursued benevolent politics, the politics of trust and love, on the basis of the philosophy of loving people to protect and take care of their destiny,  and thus glorified the revolutionary struggle for independence as a true cause of love for human beings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Indeed, he was the universally recognized veteran leader who led the socialist cause in all fields, including the building of the party, state and armed forces and social transformation, nature-harnessing and human transformation to victory and set a leading example in the revolution in our times, thus giving a strong impetus to the process of revolutionary transformation in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As the Korean people hold the respected Kim Jong Il, a peerlessly great man, in high esteem, the history of the sun of Juche is steadily advancing, the reporter said, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Holding fast to the invariable revolutionary principle of doing everything the way the President did, he has brought about a historic turning-point in the revolutionary cause of Juche, the cause of independence of the popular masses, with his outstanding and seasoned leadership.

President's view on younger generation 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- "Let us train better and take warmer care of the younger generation for the future of the country, the future of humankind " this was the President Kim Il Sung's invariable view on the younger generation  for over 80 years of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He spared nothing for the children, considering the education of the younger generation as an important issue related to the future destiny of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He built schools for the children's corps members in guerrilla bases during the arduous anti-Japanese armed struggle and took the measure of building nurseries, kindergartens and schools for the younger generation after the liberation of the country in August Juche 34 (1945). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
When the first creche (March 8 Creche) was built in Pyongyang, the President spared time to visit it and instructed officials of the central committee of the Communist Party of North Korea to send a carpet from it to the creche for the children who started to walk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Though there were a lot of urgent problems to be solved to build a new society, he placed the problem of pencil on top of the agenda of the provisional people's committee of North Korea and allocated 17 percent of the state budget for education including building and repair of schools in 1946 when the country's financial situation was difficult. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President deemed it the greatest pride and happiness to love and take care of the younger generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He brought up a war orphan in the supreme command during the hard-fought Fatherland Liberation War (1950-1953) and let the cabinet adopt a decision on setting up schools for children of the fallen fighters and war orphans.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In one year he sent priceless tonics to the weak pupils whom he met on his way for on-the-spot guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On April 1, 1954, which marked a new school year, he visited Pyongyang primary school no. 19 (Songbuk primary school at present). Learning that its school building was not in good shape, he took a measure of letting its teaching staff use the building of the ministry of industry, which was near it, as their school building. He visited at least 100 primary and senior middle schools from the time of the liberation of the country to the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The children in the DPRK are treated as "king" of the country thanks to his noble view on the younger generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They are growing up to be reliable successors to the revolutionary cause of Juche, receiving free compulsory education.

History of nationalization of major industries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A work for the nationalization of major industries was energetically pushed ahead with in Korea after the liberation of the country in August Juche 34 (1945). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The building of new democratic Korea could be sped up and an independent development of the national economy ensured only when the working class of Korea owned the key economic branches which had been held by the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Worker's Party of Korea defined in a unique manner objects, principle and method of the nationalization in conformity with the specific conditions at that time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The principle was to confiscate without compensation all factories, mines, railways, communications, banks, trade and cultural establishments, etc., which had been in the hands of the Japanese imperialists and comprador capitalists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK saw to it that the nationalization did not sweep away the ownership of the national capitalists and minor entrepreneurs but their activities were encouraged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It took a measure of investing workers' committees organized at factories and enterprises with power to confiscate what had been owned by the Japanese imperialists and comprador capitalists and taking it over before promulgating the law on the nationalization of the major industries to declare by law that the ownership and use of the confiscated major industrial facilities and economic establishments went into the hands of the working class and all other people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK put up the slogan "Factories to the workers" and roused them to the struggle for the nationalization of the major industries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Along with this, it made sure that trade unions and factory committees were organized to awaken and unite the working class politically and organizationally. As a result, trade unions were organized in the railways, metal, machine-building  and all other industries and the factory committees formed at every factory and enterprise in a matter of three months. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The workers brought under their control all the industrial establishments which had been owned by the Japanese imperialists, comprador capitalists, pro-Japanese and traitors to the nation while smashing the maneuvers of the reactionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As a result, the provisional people's committee of North Korea promulgated the law on the nationalization of the major industries on August 10, 1946. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This marked a historical event which legally confirmed and consolidated the conversion of the ownership of all the major industries in Korea into all-people, state ownership.

Overseas Korean artistes perform 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- An art troupe of Koreans in Japan, an art troupe of the International United Confederation of Koreans and an art troupe of Koreans in China participating in the 18th April Spring Friendship Art Festival began their performances at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre on April 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Overseas Korean artistes put on the stage colorful programs, including songs and dances praising the immortal revolutionary feats performed by the President Kim Il Sung, a peerlessly great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The art troupe of Koreans in Japan presented solo and dance "When Thinking of the Leader" fully reflecting the faith that President Kim Il Sung is always with us. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Mini-Haegum solo and dance "Warm Is Motherland's Love," etc, performed by its artistes paid high tribute to the President who protected the destiny of the overseas compatriots and bestowed all sorts of benevolence upon them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In man's vocal solo "We Began From Ruins" the art troupe of the International United Confederation of Koreans sang high praises of the immortal exploits performed by the President in building the people-centered socialist system on this land, deeply impressing the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Women soloists of the art troupe of Koreans in china presented songs "Sun of 21st Century" and "O Marshal's Care" in which they truthfully represented the boundless national pride and honor of holding General Secretary Kim Jong Il in high esteem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A woman soloist sang with her rich voice "Only One Stem" highly lauding the revolutionary feats of the indomitable communist revolutionary fighter Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Overseas Korean artistes put on the stage woman vocal solo "I Miss the Benevolent Leader Very Much," dance "We Live Believing In You As In Heaven," mixed chorus "Let's Carry Forward Intention" and solo dance "Dance With Two Fans" to be acclaimed by the audience.

Greetings to Queen of Denmark 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, today sent a message of greetings to Queen Margrethe II of Denmark on the occasion of its National Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message extended warm congratulations to Margrethe II and the Danish people on the occasion of the national day, the birthday of the Queen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It sincerely wished the Queen good health and happiness  on her 60th birthday and the  Danish people progress and prosperity  and expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms.

Greetings to Syrian President
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, today sent a message of greetings to Hafez al Assad, President of Syria, on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message extended warm congratulations to the President, government and people of Syria  on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that the Korean people are sincerely rejoiced over the great successes made by the Syrian Arab people in building a new, independent and prosperous Syria under the correct leadership of the President,  the message extended full support to the principled stand of the Syrian people on retaking the occupied Golan Heights and achieving mideast peace comprehensively and fairly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It expressed the belief that the excellent relations of friendship and cooperation and the bonds of solidarity between the two countries would grow stronger and develop and sincerely wished the President good health and happiness and the Syrian people greater progress and prosperity.

Greetings to Senegalese delegations and overseas compatriots
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun sent a message of greetings to Cheikh Tidiane Gadio upon his appointment as Minister of Foreign Affairs and overseas compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms in the interests of the two peoples and sincerely wished him great success in his new work.

Greetings to Prime Minister of Senegal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Hong Song Nam, premier of the DPRK cabinet, sent a message of greetings to Moustapha Niasse upon his appointment as Prime Minister of Senegal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would develop still further and sincerely wished him great success in his responsible work.

Yang Hyong Sop meets African regional delegates to IIJI meeting
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, met and conversed with African regional delegates to the 15th meeting of the board of the International Institute of the Juche Idea (IIJI) at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. They were Chango Machyo, director of the board of the IIJI and senior advisor to the Ugandan President, Joseph F. Mbwiliza, director of the board of the IIJI and chairman of the State Standing Survey Committee of Tanzania, and Andria Velonandro Anselme, chairman of the Malagasy National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They said that the DPRK which is advancing under the uplifted banner of the Juche idea is a beacon of hope for the world's progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President Kim Il Sung showed great concern and extended solidarity to the just struggle of the African people till the last moment of his life, they noted, adding today the great leader Kim Jong Il is encouraging them in their struggle.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il from Cambodian and Sri Lankan  political parties
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received gifts from the central committees of the People's Party of Cambodia and the Sri Lanka Communist Party on the occasion of Sun's Day, the birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The gifts were handed to officials concerned by member of the standing commission of the central committee of the People's Party of Cambodia and vice-chairman of the control committee of the PPC Ney Pena, who is heading a delegation of the PPC, and general secretary of the central committee of the Sri Lanka Communist Party Darrel Chandra raja Collure on a visit to the DPRK.
